Phoenix Fighters Demo 1.1
-------------------------

This is a limited demo version of Phoenix Fighters, the soon to be
released Amiga game from Bitwise/Alive mediasoft Ltd. In this demo
there are three one player missions, one two player mission, one
gate race, one gem race and one dog fight level with a timeout.
Furthermore, only five of the twenty ships are available.

Final version will include:
  80 One Player Missions
  50 Two Player Missions
  20 One/Two Player Gate Races
  20 One/Two Player Gem Races
  40 Dog Fight Levels


Phoenix Fighters is scheduled for release in April 1999. You may
preorder your copy at £14.99 (+P&P) by mail, email or phone:

Mail:     Alive mediasoft Ltd.
          PO Box 940
          Nottingham
          England

E-mail:   jenniealive@innotts.co.uk

Phone:    +44 (0)1623 467 579


Please report any bugs at dva95rng@cs.umu.se
For more information, please visit the Phoenix Fighters' web site,
hosted by the development team Bitwise at:
http://www.cs.umu.se/~dva95rng/pf.html


Short info on the game controls:
o Dock your ship by landing at the starting base and pull joystick back.
o While docking you can buy, sell and repair weapons, equipments and ships.
  In the top box, select between buy, sell and repair with joystick left
  and select weapon, equipment or ship with joystick right. The selected
  action is performed by pressing fire in the box below.


Enjoy the Demo of Phoenix Fighters!

/Bitwise 24-Mar-1999  - Robert Norberg
